/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `exprℝ -/
/-- If a real differentiable map `f` is conformal at a point `x`,
    then it preserves the angles at that point. -/
theorem conformal_at.preserves_angle {f : E → F} {x : E} {f' : «expr →L[ ] » E (exprℝ) F} (h : has_fderiv_at f f' x)
    (H : conformal_at f x) (u v : E) : angle (f' u) (f' v) = angle u v :=
  let ⟨f₁, h₁, c⟩ := H
  h₁.unique h ▸ is_conformal_map.preserves_angle c u v
#align conformal_at.preserves_angle conformal_at.preserves_angle
